\begin_layout Subsection*
The Standard Library Atlas
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A language is only as useful as its toolkit.
 Scala's standard library is designed to be "batteries included" but "type-safe by default." This reference covers the essential modules you will touch every day.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
1.
 Any,
 AnyVal,
 and AnyRef:
 The Hierarchy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At the top of the world sits 
\family typewriter
Any
\family default
.
 Everything in Scala inherits from it.
 It splits into two branches:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
AnyVal
\series default
:
 Primitive types like 
\family typewriter
Int
\family default
,
 
\family typewriter
Double
\family default
,
 
\family typewriter
Boolean
\family default
,
 and 
\family typewriter
Unit
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
AnyRef
\series default
:
 All objects (the equivalent of 
\family typewriter
java.lang.Object
\family default
).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
2.
 The Collection Module (
\family typewriter
scala.collection
\family default
)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The "Crown Jewel" of the library.
 It is split into 
\series bold
immutable
\series default
 (default) and 
\series bold
mutable
\series default
 packages.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Seq / List
\series default
:
 Ordered sequences.
 Use 
\family typewriter
List
\family default
 for functional recursion and 
\family typewriter
Vector
\family default
 for random access performance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Set
\series default
:
 Unordered collections of unique elements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Map
\series default
:
 Key-value pairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
val fruits = List("Apple",
 "Banana")
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
val prices = Map("Apple" -> 0.99,
 "Banana" -> 0.50)
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
// The power of the library is in the combinators:
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
val shoppingList = fruits.flatMap(f => prices.get(f).map(p => s"$f:
 $p"))
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
3.
 The Option,
 Either,
 and Try Modules
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These are the "Safety" containers that replace 
\family typewriter
null
\family default
 and 
\family typewriter
exceptions
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Option
\series default
:
 
\family typewriter
Some(value)
\family default
 or 
\family typewriter
None
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Either
\series default
:
 
\family typewriter
Right(value)
\family default
 (the "right" way) or 
\family typewriter
Left(error)
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Try
\series default
:
 
\family typewriter
Success(value)
\family default
 or 
\family typewriter
Failure(exception)
\family default
.
 Use this when interacting with legacy Java code that throws.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
4.
 Future and Concurrency (
\family typewriter
scala.concurrent
\family default
)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Scala makes asynchronous programming "Pragmatic" using 
\family typewriter
Future
\family default
.
 It represents a value that will eventually be available.
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
import scala.concurrent.Future
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
import scala.concurrent.ExecutionContext.Implicits.global
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
val asyncTask = Future {
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
  Thread.sleep(1000)
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
  "Data Loaded"
\end_layout

\begin_layout LyX-Code
}
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
5.
 StringOps:
 The String Extension
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In Scala,
 a 
\family typewriter
String
\family default
 is technically a 
\family typewriter
java.lang.String
\family default
,
 but Scala uses 
\series bold
Extension Methods
\series default
 to give it functional powers like .
\family typewriter
map
\family default
,
 
\family typewriter
.filter
\family default
,
 and 
\family typewriter
.splitAt
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
6.
 Numeric and Math (
\family typewriter
scala.math
\family default
)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Standard mathematical functions (sin,
 cos,
 max,
 min) and 
\family typewriter
BigDecimal
\family default
 / 
\family typewriter
BigInt
\family default
 for high-precision financial calculations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
7.
 The Predef Object
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is a secret object called 
\family typewriter
Predef
\family default
 that is imported automatically into every Scala file.
 It provides:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
println
\family default
 (aliased from 
\family typewriter
Console.println
\family default
)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
identity
\family default
 (a function that returns its input)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\backslash
item Type aliases like 
\family typewriter
String
\family default
,
 
\family typewriter
Map
\family default
,
 and 
\family typewriter
Set
\family default
.
\end_layout

